  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to discover whether arthroscopic surgery is helpful in
      controlling the symptoms of osteoarthritis of the knee.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Although arthroscopic surgery has been widely used for osteoarthritis of the knee, scientific
      evidence to support its efficacy is lacking. This study will compare optimized physical and
      medical therapy alone with arthroscopic treatment in addition to optimized physical and
      medical therapy.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
